# Create Handler Rule

Use when creating a new HTTP handler in masterfabric_go. Equivalent of "create-view" in Flutter.

## Directory Structure

```
internal/infrastructure/http/handler/<context>/
├── handler.go          # Handler struct + all HTTP methods
```

## Step 1: Create DTO

File: `internal/application/<context>/dto/<entity>_dto.go`

```go
package dto

type CreateEntityRequest struct {
    Name   string `json:"name" validate:"required"`
    Status string `json:"status"`
}

type EntityInfo struct {
    ID        uuid.UUID `json:"id"`
    Name      string    `json:"name"`
    Status    string    `json:"status"`
    CreatedAt time.Time `json:"created_at"`
}
```

## Step 2: Create Use Case

File: `internal/application/<context>/usecase/create_entity.go`

```go
type CreateEntityUseCase struct {
    repo     repository.EntityRepository
    eventBus events.EventBus
}

func NewCreateEntityUseCase(repo repository.EntityRepository, eventBus events.EventBus) *CreateEntityUseCase {
    return &CreateEntityUseCase{repo: repo, eventBus: eventBus}
}

func (uc *CreateEntityUseCase) Execute(ctx context.Context, req dto.CreateEntityRequest) (*dto.EntityInfo, error) {
    entity := &model.Entity{Name: req.Name, Status: req.Status}
    if err := uc.repo.Create(ctx, entity); err != nil {
        return nil, err
    }
    _ = uc.eventBus.Publish(ctx, events.TopicXxx, event)
    return &dto.EntityInfo{ID: entity.ID, ...}, nil
}
```

## Step 3: Create Handler

File: `internal/infrastructure/http/handler/<context>/handler.go`

```go
type Handler struct {
    createEntityUC *usecase.CreateEntityUseCase
    entityRepo     repository.EntityRepository
}

func NewHandler(createUC *usecase.CreateEntityUseCase, repo repository.EntityRepository) *Handler {
    return &Handler{createEntityUC: createUC, entityRepo: repo}
}

func (h *Handler) CreateEntity(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
    var req dto.CreateEntityRequest
    if err := validator.DecodeAndValidate(r, &req); err != nil {
        response.JSON(w, http.StatusBadRequest, map[string]string{"error": err.Error()})
        return
    }
    result, err := h.createEntityUC.Execute(r.Context(), req)
    if err != nil {
        response.Error(w, err)
        return
    }
    response.Created(w, result)
}
```

## Step 4: Register Route

File: `internal/infrastructure/http/router/router.go`

```go
r.Route("/entities", func(r chi.Router) {
    r.Post("/", deps.EntityHandler.CreateEntity)
    r.Get("/", deps.EntityHandler.ListEntities)
    r.Route("/{entityId}", func(r chi.Router) {
        r.Get("/", deps.EntityHandler.GetEntity)
        r.Put("/", deps.EntityHandler.UpdateEntity)
        r.Delete("/", deps.EntityHandler.DeleteEntity)
    })
})
```

## Step 5: Wire in main.go

```go
entityRepo := postgresEntity.NewEntityRepo(db)
createEntityUC := entityUC.NewCreateEntityUseCase(entityRepo, eventBus)
deps.EntityHandler = entityHandler.NewHandler(createEntityUC, entityRepo)
```

## Checklist

- [ ] DTO with validation tags in `application/<context>/dto/`
- [ ] Use case with `Execute()` method in `application/<context>/usecase/`
- [ ] Handler with chi URL params in `infrastructure/http/handler/<context>/`
- [ ] Route registered in `router.go`
- [ ] Dependencies wired in `main.go`
- [ ] Error responses use `response.Error(w, err)`
- [ ] Success responses use `response.JSON()`, `response.Created()`, or `response.NoContent()`
